

How to add new node in the 2 node pcs cluster

Adding a new node to an existing 2-node PCS (Pacemaker/Corosync) cluster is a structured process. Below is a clean, step-by-step guide you can follow on RHEL / Rocky / Alma Linux (PCS cluster).

🧩 Current Setup Assumption
Existing nodes: node1, node2

New node to add: node3

Cluster name: mycluster

✅ Step 1: Prepare the New Node (node3)
Run on node3:

# Set hostname
hostnamectl set-hostname node3

# Add all nodes in /etc/hosts (on ALL nodes)
vi /etc/hosts
Example:

192.168.1.101 node1
192.168.1.102 node2
192.168.1.103 node3
✅ Step 2: Install Required Packages
On node3:

dnf install -y pcs pacemaker corosync fence-agents-all
✅ Step 3: Enable and Start pcsd
systemctl enable --now pcsd
✅ Step 4: Set Password for hacluster User
Run on ALL nodes (node1, node2, node3):

passwd hacluster
⚠️ Use the same password everywhere.

✅ Step 5: Authenticate the New Node
Run from any existing node (node1):

pcs host auth node3 -u hacluster -p <password>
Or authenticate all together:

pcs host auth node1 node2 node3 -u hacluster -p <password>
✅ Step 6: Add Node to Cluster
Run on node1:

pcs cluster node add node3
✅ Step 7: Sync and Start Cluster on New Node
pcs cluster start node3
Enable cluster on boot:

pcs cluster enable node3
✅ Step 8: Verify Cluster Status
pcs status
You should now see:

Online: [ node1 node2 node3 ]
⚠️ Important Considerations
1. Quorum Changes (Very Important)
2-node cluster → quorum = 2

3-node cluster → quorum = 2 (majority)

Check:

pcs quorum status
2. Update Corosync Config (if needed)
Usually handled automatically, but verify:

pcs cluster config
3. Fencing (STONITH)
If fencing is configured, ensure:

New node is added to fencing device

Example:

pcs stonith update <stonith_name> pcmk_host_list="node1,node2,node3"
4. Resource Constraints
Check if constraints need update:

pcs constraint
You may need to adjust location constraints for node3.

🧪 Optional: Test Failover
After adding node3:

pcs node standby node1
Check if resources move properly.

🚀 Summary
Prepare node3 (hostname, hosts file)

Install cluster packages

Start pcsd and set hacluster password

Authenticate node

Add node to cluster

Start and verify

Adjust quorum, fencing, constraints

