For 4 nodes, qdisk will be requiored

Good question — this is where many people get confused.

🧠 Short Answer
No, qdisk (qdevice) is NOT required for a 4-node cluster.
But it is recommended in many cases.

⚖️ How quorum works in a 4-node cluster
Total votes = 4

Quorum (majority) = 3

Scenarios:
Situation	Result
1 node fails (3 nodes alive)	✅ Quorum maintained
2 nodes fail (2 nodes alive)	❌ No quorum
Split brain (2 vs 2)	❌ No quorum on either side
👉 The problem is the 2 vs 2 split — no side has majority.

🔥 So what happens without qdevice?
Cluster will stop resources (default behavior)

This is safe but causes downtime

✔ No data corruption
❌ But service interruption

🧩 Where qdevice helps
If you add a qdevice (external arbitrator):

Total votes = 5 (4 nodes + 1 qdevice)

Quorum = 3

Now in split (2 vs 2):
One side gets qdevice vote → 3 votes ✅

Other side → 2 votes ❌

👉 Result: one side survives, no downtime

🔥 Role of Fencing (Still Mandatory)
Even with or without qdevice:

✔ Fencing (STONITH) is always required

It prevents split-brain data corruption

✅ Best Practice Recommendation
For 4-node cluster:
✔ Fencing → MANDATORY

✔ qdevice → RECOMMENDED (not mandatory)

🚦 When you SHOULD use qdevice
Use qdevice if:

High availability is critical (banking, production DB, etc.)

You want to avoid downtime during 2–2 split

Multi-site cluster

🚫 When you can skip qdevice
Non-critical workloads

Occasional downtime is acceptable

Simpler setup preferred

🧾 Final Conclusion
3-node cluster → No qdevice needed

4-node cluster → qdevice optional but recommended

Fencing → always mandatory

