What are steps to remove one node in 2 nodes cluster and new 2nd node

Got it — you want to replace one node in a 2-node PCS cluster (remove old node2 and add new node2). This needs to be done carefully to avoid downtime or split-brain.

🔄 Scenario
Current cluster: node1, node2

You want:

❌ Remove node2

✅ Add new node (say node3) as second node

⚠️ Important Precautions
Before starting:

✔ Ensure cluster is healthy

✔ Move all resources to node1

✔ Confirm fencing is working

✅ Step 1: Move Resources to node1
pcs node standby node2
Check:

pcs status
👉 Ensure all resources are running on node1

✅ Step 2: Stop Cluster on node2
On node2:

pcs cluster stop node2
✅ Step 3: Remove node2 from Cluster
Run on node1:

pcs cluster node remove node2
Verify:

pcs status
👉 Now only node1 should be in cluster

⚠️ Step 4: Adjust Quorum Policy (VERY IMPORTANT)
Now cluster has only 1 node, so quorum will be lost.

Temporarily allow it:

pcs property set no-quorum-policy=ignore
✅ Step 5: Prepare New Node (node3)
On node3:

1. Set hostname
hostnamectl set-hostname node3
2. Update /etc/hosts (on BOTH nodes)
192.168.1.101 node1
192.168.1.103 node3
3. Install packages
dnf install -y pcs pacemaker corosync fence-agents-all
4. Start pcsd
systemctl enable --now pcsd
5. Set password
passwd hacluster
(Same password as node1)

✅ Step 6: Authenticate New Node
On node1:

pcs host auth node3 -u hacluster -p <password>
✅ Step 7: Add New Node to Cluster
pcs cluster node add node3
✅ Step 8: Start Cluster on New Node
pcs cluster start node3
pcs cluster enable node3
✅ Step 9: Restore Quorum Policy
After node3 joins:

pcs property set no-quorum-policy=stop
✅ Step 10: Update Fencing (CRITICAL)
If STONITH exists, update it:

pcs stonith update <stonith_name> pcmk_host_list="node1,node3"
✅ Step 11: Verify Cluster
pcs status
pcs quorum status
Expected:

Online: [ node1 node3 ]
🧪 Optional: Test Failover
pcs node standby node1
👉 Check if resources move to node3

🚨 Common Mistakes to Avoid
❌ Forgetting to update fencing → can cause split-brain

❌ Not setting no-quorum-policy=ignore temporarily

❌ Not moving resources before removing node

❌ Mismatch in /etc/hosts

🧾 Final Flow Summary
Move resources → node1

Stop & remove node2

Temporarily ignore quorum

Prepare node3

Authenticate & add node3

Start cluster on node3

Restore quorum policy

Update fencing

