rocky-node2: Unable to connect to rocky-node2, check if pcsd is running there or try setting higher timeout with --request-timeout option (Failed to connect to rocky-node2 port 2224: Connection refused)
Error: unable to stop all nodes

This error is very common during node removal/replacement. Let’s break it down clearly:

❗ Error Explanation
Unable to connect to rocky-node2
Failed to connect to port 2224: Connection refused
Error: unable to stop all nodes
👉 Meaning:

pcsd service is NOT running on rocky-node2

Or node is already down / unreachable

PCS cannot communicate to stop cluster services cleanly

🧠 Important Understanding
When removing a node:

PCS tries to contact that node

If node is already down → removal fails with this error

👉 But you can still remove it forcefully

✅ Solution (Force Remove Node)
Run this on active node (rocky-node1):

pcs cluster node remove rocky-node2 --force
🔥 If Above Command Fails
Use manual cleanup:

1. Remove node from corosync config
pcs cluster config
Then:

pcs cluster node remove rocky-node2 --force --skip-offline
2. If still stuck → edit config manually
vi /etc/corosync/corosync.conf
Remove entry of rocky-node2 under:

nodelist {
    node {
        ring0_addr: rocky-node1
    }
    # REMOVE THIS BLOCK
    node {
        ring0_addr: rocky-node2
    }
}
3. Reload cluster config
pcs cluster reload corosync
⚠️ Very Important After Removal
1. Check cluster status
pcs status
2. Fix quorum issue (since now 1 node)
pcs property set no-quorum-policy=ignore
3. Clean any leftover resources
pcs node cleanup rocky-node2
4. Update fencing (CRITICAL)
pcs stonith update <stonith_name> pcmk_host_list="rocky-node1"
👉 If you skip this → cluster may try fencing non-existing node

🧾 Root Cause Summary
Issue	Reason
Connection refused	pcsd not running / node down
Removal failed	PCS expects node to respond
✅ Best Practice
Before removing node (next time):

pcs node standby rocky-node2
pcs cluster stop rocky-node2
systemctl stop pcsd
Then remove → no error

🚀 Final Outcome
✔ Node removed even if offline

✔ Cluster continues on single node

✔ Ready to add new node

